# Optional: merge into your shell profile or OpenClaw workspace `.env`.
# When a host exports a narrow AINL_HOST_ADAPTER_ALLOWLIST (e.g. only `core`),
# set this so AINL graphs may still use adapters declared in the IR (`web`, `http`, …).
# Denylist and runner/MCP security profiles still apply.
# ArmaraOS desktop + scheduled `ainl run` set this by default when unset (see armaraos/docs/scheduled-ainl.md).
# AINL_ALLOW_IR_DECLARED_ADAPTERS=1
